The Swedish-born producer and DJ known as Avicii has been found dead in Oman. 
Publicist Diana Baron said in a statement that the 28-year-old DJ, born Tim Bergling, was in Muscat, Oman, AP reports.
Baron said in a statement: “It is with profound sorrow that we announce the loss of Tim Bergling, also known as Avicii. He was found dead in Muscat, Oman this Friday afternoon local time, April 20th. The family is devastated and we ask everyone to please respect their need for privacy in this difficult time. No further statements will be given,” TMZ reports.
Avicii was a pioneer of the contemporary Electronic Dance Movement and a rare DJ capable of worldwide arena tours. He won two MTV Music Awards, one Billboard Music Award and earned two Grammy nominations. His biggest hit was Le7els.
His death comes just days after he was nominated for a Billboard Music Award for top dance/electronic album for his EP Avicii (01).
His hits include Wake Me Up! The Days and You Make Me.
